post_text:
Over the next several days, we will be introducing you to our new staff. The first one is from our new first grade teacher Jocelyn Lewis.

Hello! My name is Jocelyn Lewis and I will be the first grade teacher this year. This is my first year teaching. I recently graduated from UNI with a degree and elementary and middle level education. I grew up in Greene, Iowa with my parents and my older brother. I am currently living in Grundy Center. I love being outside and traveling. I'm so excited to teach at GMG and can't wait to get to know the community and everyone in it!

post_text:
Just a reminder that GMG K-3 Summer Learning is this week (July 27th-31st) from 9:00am to 12:00pm for those who already registered their children in this program.

Please remember:

- Drop off and pick up will be at the main entrance (Teachers will begin to let students in at 8:50am)

- There will not be any school provided transportation at this time

- Students are encouraged to wear masks but are not required

- Parents are not allowed to enter the building at this time

- Students do not need to bring any materials with them, but may want to bring a water bottle

- Students will be split into small groups based on our daily numbers

- Students will learn literacy skills in a classroom setting

Thank you for your patience and cooperation. We look forward to working with your children this week! :)

post_text:
Substitute teachers wanted! The AEA has created an additional (online) course in August for anyone interested in becoming authorized as a substitute teacher.

According to the AEA:

Substitute Authorization Course #3405
Section #284165
Dates: August 17-21
Time: Daily 9-12:00 via zoom
Cost: $130 ($100 for course and $30 textbook fee, textbook will be mailed to participants prior to start date). After the course, participants will need to apply for licensure through the BOEE at a cost of $160.
To register: https://aealearning.truenorthlogic.com/ you must log in or create a free account, enter course # in search box and follow directions to register.

For more information, you can contact Heather Staebell at Central Rivers AEA- hstaebell@centralriversaea.org

More information on the program and eligibility for obtaining licensure as a substitute teacher can be found in the flyer-

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1F1eqTBHM-vjND5lCUMgnrAJc3fL7bcvy/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
Before we were dismissed from school this year, 4T and 5T partnered with Project Jack and Make a Wish Foundation. Both classes were provided a grant of $250 each from Project Jack, and it was decided that we would use this money to provide supplies to Make a Wish. With the funds provided, we gathered six themed baskets including "Beach Vibes," "Travel," "Fun and Games," "Journal writing," "Art," and "I Love my BFF (Best Furry Friend)," and filled them with supplies. We will be delivering the bags soon to Make a Wish.

A special thank you to Jane Smith for helping us decorate the bags!!

The new Iowa School Performance Report has been released. The report can be found at: https://www.iaschoolperformance.gov/ECP/Home/Index GMG Elementary is proud to report that we received a commendable rating from the Iowa Department of Education. That rating is in the top half of all possible ratings. This is the second year in a row we were rated at that level. The possible levels are: Exceptional, High Performing, Commendable, Acceptable, Needs Improvement, and Priority. Even though we are proud of that rating, we will continue to look for ways to improve.

post_text: GMG Elementary decided to pay it forward today. All classes, PK-6, participated in an Outreach Program where the students packaged nutritious meals for the needy. GMG Elementary would like to thank Mrs. Sabus, Karen Jackson, Diana Thorn, Alan Mullikin, and Nathan Holven for volunteering their time to help out with the process.

post_text:
Dear GMG Families,

Starting on November 4, we will extend our after school daycare hours until 5:30. Please make sure your child is picked up by that 5:30 time.

Also, as a reminder:

*If there is dismissal of school because of weather, we will not have after school daycare.

*If there is a late start due to weather, there will not be before school daycare.

*On days when there is no school, we will not offer daycare.

*Finally, if there is an early out before a break, after school daycare will not be offered.

post_text:
Please pass this information on...

Looking for a way to showcase your talents for a good cause? Why not join GMG Elementary in helping us fundraise for The Outreach Program? We are looking for businesses, organizations, and individuals who are willing to donate items for our basket auction. On November 13th and 14th, the night of conferences, GMG will be hosting an auction. Simply place your items in a basket and they will be auctioned off on both nights of conferences. This is a great way to promote your business and talents to the community. Baskets can be either theme related, such as skin products, toys, cooking, hunting, or items related to your business. All proceeds will go towards the purchase of food and materials to be used for our food packaging event on December 17th. The food will be packaged by the elementary students and given to local organizations to help those in need. We are looking forward to this event! Contact the school for more information on this project!

post_text:
END OF YEAR

Dear GMG Elementary,

Looking ahead to the end of the year, I wanted to get some information out to you. The following bullet points are things that I would like you to pay attention to.

• We will have a 2:20 dismiss on May 24 since it is the Friday before Memorial Day. There will be no daycare after school on this day.
• We will also continue the Wednesday 2:20 dismiss on May 29 even though it is the last Wednesday before the end of the school year.
• The last day of school is May 31. We will be having a 2:20 dismiss that day. There will be no daycare after school.
• There will be no school on Monday May 27 because of Memorial Day.
• Preschool graduation is Wednesday May 29 at 5:30
• Field day for the elementary is Thursday May 30 in the morning. We will also have our pork burger lunch.
• Friday May 31 is the rain date for field day.

The other winner of the GMG Student Leadership Award is Zach.

On the nomination form it says: "Zach is being a good leader and role model at GMG. He volunteers every day 1-3 to meet with three first graders. He is building a positive peer relationship with these first graders and setting goals with them. He is encouraging and helping them to monitor their daily goals. Zach is modeling strong leadership skill by being responsible, accountable, and reliable to himself and these three first graders."
